### Linting & Formatting
- Lint code: Use `ruff check .` and `ruff check . --fix`
- Format code: `ruff format .`

## Code Style Guidelines

### Imports
- Standard library imports first, third-party imports second, local imports last
- Group imports by type and sort alphabetically
- Use Pathlib for file paths, not os

### Formatting
- Use type annotations for function parameters and return values
- Use snake_case for variables, functions, and methods
- Use PascalCase for classes
- Line length should follow ruff standards (88 characters)

### Error Handling
- Use try/except blocks with specific exception types
- Log errors with loguru
